    "headline": "Oracle’s AI Round Trip Revenue Raises Questions On Cloud Growth Quality",
    "summary": "Analysts are raising concerns about so called AI round trip accounting practices at Big Tech, including Oracle, where investments in AI startups reportedly cycle back as cloud revenue. These arrangements involve funding unprofitable AI groups such as OpenAI and Anthropic, which then commit to spend heavily on cloud infrastructure. While current rules allow this treatment, critics warn it may inflate reported cloud growth and obscure the underlying quality of revenue. For investors watching...",
